d `remediated` statuses.\n\n\n**Defining the `DocItem` Interface**\n\nI've defined the `DocItem` interface, meticulously mapping API responses to it. Specifically, I'm transforming various document properties, including `id`, `name`, `size`, `format`, and various identifiers. I'm focusing on handling potential null values and ensuring consistent ID formats. I'm also implementing logic for the status mapping and handling edge cases like missing `lastUpdated` dates. The use of `toLowerCase()` and the ternary operator are vital here.\n\n\n**Fetching API Data**\n\nI'm now implementing the actual data fetching within a `try...catch` block. I'm leveraging `Promise.all` to fetch governance and documents concurrently. I'm handling authentication by checking for expired tokens and redirecting to the login page if needed. After the fetches complete, I'm checking the responses for success and using `mapApiGovToPolicy`, `mapApiGovToOversight`, and `mapApiDocToDocItem` to format the data. Error handling is also in place to provide informative messages.\n\n\n"}}
